==English==
===Etymology===
coalitus Latin, mix together.
Used by U.S. President George Bush in the beginning of the 20th century to identify a unique group of nations who joined the United States for negotiated compensation in the invasion of Iraq when traditional allies said the invasion was illegal.

===Noun===
#  A temporary group or union of organizations usually for a particular advantage.
#  Any of a small group of nations offering soldiers to the United States in support of an invasion of Iraq because of compensation rather than an alliance.